Package com.googlecode.cqengine.index.support

Interface SortedKeyStatisticsIndex<A extends Comparable<A>,​O>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Index<O>, KeyStatisticsIndex<A,​O>, ModificationListener<O>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SortedKeyStatisticsAttributeIndex<A,​O>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DiskIndex, NavigableIndex, OffHeapIndex, PartialDiskIndex, PartialNavigableIndex, PartialOffHeapIndex, PartialSortedKeyStatisticsAttributeIndex, PartialSQLiteIndex, SimplifiedSQLiteIndex, SQLiteDiskIdentityIndex, SQLiteIdentityIndex, SQLiteIndex, SQLiteOffHeapIdentityIndex
    public interface SortedKeyStatisticsIndex<A extends Comparable<A>,​O>
extends KeyStatisticsIndex<A,​O>
    An index which allows the set of distinct keys to be queried in sorted order, and which can return statistics on the number of objects stored for each key. Created by niall.gallagher on 09/01/2015.

      • getKeysAndValues

        CloseableIterable<KeyValue<A,​O>> getKeysAndValues​(QueryOptions queryOptions)
        Returns the keys and corresponding values for those keys in the index. Note the same key will be returned multiple times if more than one object has the same key. Also the same value might be returned multiple times, each time for a different key, if the index is built on a multi-value attribute.
        Specified by:
        getKeysAndValues in interface KeyStatisticsIndex<A extends Comparable<A>,​O>
        Parameters:
        queryOptions - Optional parameters for the query
        Returns:
        The keys and corresponding values for those keys in the index, in ascending order of key

      • getKeysAndValues

        CloseableIterable<KeyValue<A,​O>> getKeysAndValues​(A lowerBound,
                                                        boolean lowerInclusive,
                                                        A upperBound,
                                                        boolean upperInclusive,
                                                        QueryOptions queryOptions)
        Returns the keys within an optional range and corresponding values for those keys in the index. Note the same key will be returned multiple times if more than one object has the same key. Also the same value might be returned multiple times, each time for a different key, if the index is built on a multi-value attribute.
        Parameters:
        lowerBound - The lower bound for the keys returned, or null if no lower bound should be applied
        lowerInclusive - true if the lowerBound is inclusive, false if exclusive
        upperBound - The upper bound for the keys returned, or null if no upper bound should be applied
        upperInclusive - true if the lowerBound is inclusive, false if exclusive
        queryOptions - Optional parameters for the query
        Returns:
        The keys and corresponding values for those keys in the index, in ascending order of key
